# Modular Gameplay Systems Plugin

[![Unreal Engine](https://img.shields.io/badge/Unreal%20Engine-5.3-blue)](https://www.unrealengine.com/)
[![C++](https://img.shields.io/badge/C++-20-orange)](https://isocpp.org/)
[![Plugin](https://img.shields.io/badge/Type-Gameplay%20Plugin-purple)](https://docs.unrealengine.com/5.3/en-US/plugins-in-unreal-engine/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green.svg)](LICENSE)

Production-ready gameplay systems plugin showcasing clean architecture, modern C++, and comprehensive Blueprint integration for Unreal Engine 5.

## ğŸ¯ Project Overview

This plugin demonstrates professional game development practices with reusable gameplay systems, extensive documentation, and marketplace-quality code. Built to showcase SOLID principles, clean code architecture, and seamless C++/Blueprint integration.

## âœ¨ Key Features

### Inventory System
- **Generic, Data-Driven** design supporting any item type
- Template-based for type safety
- Network replication support for multiplayer
- Save/load integration
- Blueprint-friendly API

### Quest System
- Flexible objective framework
- Progress tracking and events
- Branching quest paths
- Data-driven quest definitions
- Designer-friendly tools

### Save System
- Automatic save game integration
- **Versioned save data** for updates
- Cloud save support structure
- Asynchronous loading
- Slot management

### Ability System
- Component-based abilities
- Cooldown and resource management
- Effect stacking and duration
- Network-optimized
- Visual feedback integration

