## ğŸš€ Installation

### Method 1: Plugin Installation
```bash
# Clone to your project's Plugins folder
cd YourProject/Plugins
git clone https://github.com/Azhartula/UE5-Modular-Gameplay-Systems.git

# Regenerate project files
Right-click YourProject.uproject â†’ Generate Visual Studio project files

# Build and launch
Open in Visual Studio â†’ Build â†’ Launch
```

### Method 2: Engine Plugin
```bash
# Clone to UE5 engine plugins
cd /path/to/UE_5.3/Engine/Plugins
git clone https://github.com/Azhartula/UE5-Modular-Gameplay-Systems.git
```

## ğŸ® Quick Start

### 1. Add Inventory to Character

#### C++
```cpp
#include "Inventory/InventoryComponent.h"

UCLASS()
class AMyCharacter : public ACharacter
{
    GENERATED_BODY()
    
protected:
    UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere, BlueprintReadOnly, Category="Inventory")
    UInventoryComponent* Inventory;
    
    AMyCharacter()
    {
        Inventory = CreateDefaultSubobject<UInventoryComponent>(TEXT("Inventory"));
        Inventory->SetMaxSlots(20);
    }
};
```

#### Blueprint
1. Add **Inventory Component** to your character
2. Set Max Slots in details panel
3. Use Blueprint nodes to add/remove items

### 2. Create Item Definition

```cpp
UCLASS(Blueprintable)
class UMyItemDefinition : public UItemDefinition
{
    GENERATED_BODY()
    
public:
    UPROPERTY(EditDefaultsOnly, BlueprintReadOnly, Category="Item")
    FText DisplayName = NSLOCTEXT("Items", "HealthPotion", "Health Potion");
    
    UPROPERTY(EditDefaultsOnly, BlueprintReadOnly, Category="Item")
    int32 MaxStackSize = 99;
    
    UPROPERTY(EditDefaultsOnly, BlueprintReadOnly, Category="Item")
    UTexture2D* Icon = nullptr;
};
```

### 3. Add Item to Inventory

#### C++
```cpp
void AMyCharacter::PickupItem(UItemDefinition* ItemDef, int32 Quantity)
{
    if (Inventory->CanAddItem(ItemDef, Quantity))
    {
        Inventory->AddItem(ItemDef, Quantity);
        OnItemPickedUp.Broadcast(ItemDef);
    }
}
```

#### Blueprint
![Add Item Blueprint](Docs/Images/add_item_blueprint.png)

## ğŸ“š API Examples

### Inventory System

```cpp
// Add item
bool bAdded = Inventory->AddItem(HealthPotionDef, 5);

// Remove item
bool bRemoved = Inventory->RemoveItem(HealthPotionDef, 1);

// Query inventory
int32 Count = Inventory->GetItemCount(HealthPotionDef);
TArray<UItemInstance*> AllItems = Inventory->GetAllItems();

// Events
Inventory->OnItemAdded.AddDynamic(this, &AMyClass::HandleItemAdded);
Inventory->OnItemRemoved.AddDynamic(this, &AMyClass::HandleItemRemoved);
```

### Quest System

```cpp
// Start quest
QuestComponent->StartQuest(MainQuestDef);

// Update objective
QuestComponent->UpdateObjectiveProgress(ObjectiveID, 1);

// Complete quest
QuestComponent->CompleteQuest(MainQuestDef);

// Query state
bool bActive = QuestComponent->IsQuestActive(MainQuestDef);
float Progress = QuestComponent->GetQuestProgress(MainQuestDef);

// Events
QuestComponent->OnQuestStarted.AddDynamic(this, &AMyClass::HandleQuestStarted);
QuestComponent->OnQuestCompleted.AddDynamic(this, &AMyClass::HandleQuestCompleted);
```

### Save System

```cpp
// Save game
USaveGameSubsystem* SaveSystem = GetGameInstance()->GetSubsystem<USaveGameSubsystem>();
SaveSystem->SaveGame(SlotName, [](bool bSuccess)
{
    UE_LOG(LogTemp, Log, TEXT("Save %s"), bSuccess ? TEXT("succeeded") : TEXT("failed"));
});

// Load game
SaveSystem->LoadGame(SlotName, [](USaveGameData* LoadedData)
{
    if (LoadedData)
    {
        // Restore game state
    }
});

// Auto-save
SaveSystem->SetAutoSaveEnabled(true);
SaveSystem->SetAutoSaveInterval(300.0f); // Every 5 minutes
```

### Ability System

```cpp
// Grant ability
AbilityComponent->GiveAbility(FireballAbilityClass);

// Try activate
bool bActivated = AbilityComponent->TryActivateAbility(FireballAbilityClass);

// Check cooldown
bool bOnCooldown = AbilityComponent->IsAbilityOnCooldown(FireballAbilityClass);
float RemainingTime = AbilityComponent->GetAbilityCooldownRemaining(FireballAbilityClass);

// Cancel ability
AbilityComponent->CancelAbility(FireballAbilityClass);
```

## ğŸ¨ Blueprint Integration

### Blueprint Callable Functions
```cpp
UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category="Inventory")
bool AddItem(UItemDefinition* ItemDef, int32 Quantity = 1);

UFUNCTION(BlueprintPure, Category="Inventory")
int32 GetItemCount(UItemDefinition* ItemDef) const;

UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category="Inventory")
TArray<UItemInstance*> GetAllItems() const;
```

### Blueprint Events
```cpp
UPROPERTY(BlueprintAssignable, Category="Inventory")
FOnItemAddedSignature OnItemAdded;

UPROPERTY(BlueprintAssignable, Category="Inventory")
FOnItemRemovedSignature OnItemRemoved;

UPROPERTY(BlueprintAssignable, Category="Inventory")
FOnInventoryChangedSignature OnInventoryChanged;
```

### Blueprint Implementable
```cpp
UFUNCTION(BlueprintImplementableEvent, Category="Inventory")
void OnItemUsed(UItemInstance* Item);

UFUNCTION(BlueprintNativeEvent, Category="Quest")
void OnQuestObjectiveCompleted(UQuestDefinition* Quest, int32 ObjectiveIndex);
```

