## ğŸ” Code Quality Features

### Documentation
```cpp
/**
 * Adds an item to the inventory.
 * 
 * @param ItemDefinition The definition of the item to add
 * @param Quantity The number of items to add (default: 1)
 * @return true if the item was successfully added, false otherwise
 * 
 * @note This function will attempt to stack items if possible
 * @see RemoveItem, GetItemCount
 */
UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category="Inventory")
bool AddItem(UItemDefinition* ItemDefinition, int32 Quantity = 1);
```

### Logging
```cpp
DECLARE_LOG_CATEGORY_EXTERN(LogInventory, Log, All);

UE_LOG(LogInventory, Display, TEXT("Added %d x %s to inventory"), 
    Quantity, *ItemDef->GetName());
```

### Error Handling
```cpp
if (!ItemDefinition)
{
    UE_LOG(LogInventory, Error, TEXT("AddItem: ItemDefinition is null!"));
    return false;
}

if (Quantity <= 0)
{
    UE_LOG(LogInventory, Warning, TEXT("AddItem: Invalid quantity %d"), Quantity);
    return false;
}
```

## ğŸ§ª Testing

### Unit Tests
```cpp
IMPLEMENT_SIMPLE_AUTOMATION_TEST(FInventoryAddItemTest, 
    "ModularGameplaySystems.Inventory.AddItem",
    EAutomationTestFlags::ApplicationContextMask | EAutomationTestFlags::ProductFilter)

bool FInventoryAddItemTest::RunTest(const FString& Parameters)
{
    UInventoryComponent* Inventory = NewObject<UInventoryComponent>();
    UItemDefinition* ItemDef = NewObject<UItemDefinition>();
    
    bool bAdded = Inventory->AddItem(ItemDef, 1);
    TestTrue("Item should be added", bAdded);
    TestEqual("Item count should be 1", Inventory->GetItemCount(ItemDef), 1);
    
    return true;
}
```

## ğŸŒ Network Replication

```cpp
void UInventoryComponent::GetLifetimeReplicatedProps(TArray<FLifetimeProperty>& OutLifetimeProps) const
{
    Super::GetLifetimeReplicatedProps(OutLifetimeProps);
    
    DOREPLIFETIME(UInventoryComponent, Items);
    DOREPLIFETIME(UInventoryComponent, MaxSlots);
}

void UInventoryComponent::OnRep_Items()
{
    OnInventoryChanged.Broadcast();
}
```

